725028f-a.text:
14th Avenue, north side, at 14rd Street. Shown is the white colonial mansion at the above location which was owned by A.J. Provost in 1873 and by J.P. Egan in 1891. The view is south from near 10th Avenue, across the Long -sland Railroad station. View 2 shows the barn, with weathercock on
top, on the estate.
P. L. Sperr  March 3, 1932
NO REPRODUCTIONS  Views 1,2
